AC  GenProp0061
DE  Lipoprotein system lgt/lsp/lnt
TP  SYSTEM
AU  Haft D
TH  0
CC  Some membrane proteins are anchored to the membrane by a lipid moiety 
CC  attached to a modified N-terminus rather than by a transmembrane 
CC  helix. This property describes such a system. The modifications that 
CC  take place are, cleavage of the lipoprotein signal sequence by 
CC  prolipoprotein signal peptidase (lsp) at a motif resembling L-X-G/A-C 
CC  to leave Cys as the new N-terminal residue. Modification of the Cys 
CC  sulfhydryl by prolipoprotein diacylglyceryl transferase (lgt), then 
CC  acylation of the Cys NH2 by apolipoprotein N-acyltransferase (lnt). 
--
